review_title: A Soothing Step Towards Serenity - Natural Factors Sleep Relax
review_text:
Living with an anxiety disorder can make the simple act of going to bed a daunting nightly challenge. In my search for relief, I turned to Natural Factors Sleep Relax with Valerian & Hops. The strong valerian scent is one I find quite pleasant, though it’s worth noting it may not be universally appreciated. The capsules themselves are manageable in size and easy to swallow, which is always a plus.

The blend of natural herbs is well-curated, targeting anxiety and sleep issues. I’ve found that taking these capsules does make it easier for me to drift off to sleep, though I wish the effects were more pronounced. It’s a gentle nudge rather than a push into slumber, which might be perfect for some but leaves me wanting a bit more.

One downside I’ve encountered is the capsules’ tendency to solidify over time, turning them into tiny rocks. This was unexpected and somewhat disappointing, considering the otherwise high quality of the product. Despite this, I believe the benefits merit a solid 4-star rating. It’s a product that has eased my journey to dreamland, even if it’s not the perfect solution.

Sleep Relax with Valerian & Hops, in a 90-capsule bottle, has become a vital part of my nighttime routine. This blend uniquely combines the calming effects of valerian root with the soothing properties of hops, creating a natural solution to improve sleep quality. Since incorporating it into my evenings, I've noticed a significant difference in how quickly I fall asleep and the overall restfulness of my sleep. The capsules are easy to take, and having a three-month supply ensures I can maintain this beneficial routine consistently. For anyone struggling with sleep disturbances or looking for a natural way to enhance sleep quality, Sleep Relax could offer a gentle yet effective solution.

After using Sleep Relax for a couple of weeks, I’ve noticed a significant improvement in my ability to fall asleep and stay asleep throughout the night. It combines high-quality valerian root and hops, both known for their calming properties. The capsules are free from artificial additives and are made with non-GMO ingredients, which gives me confidence in what I’m putting into my body. For the benefits I've experienced, Sleep Relax with Valerian & Hops is reasonably priced.

I sometimes take 2 an hour before bed and then the 3rd capsule right before laying down.  The 90 capsules will only be a 30 day supply.  I sometimes feel like the product hangs on the next day but wears off by noon.  I removed one star for using rice powder.  Paleo diets do not allow grains/rice.  It's hard to heal the gut with rice in several supplements.  Perhaps coconut flour or another food could be used as a filler.  I appreciate the good nights sleep so I will have to live with the rice powder for now until I can find something grain free.

The formula looks very good. Valerian helps improve sleep, promote relaxation and reduce anxiety. It appears to be safe and non-habit forming when taken at the recommended dosage. In some cases, it may be able to replace benzodiazepines and similar drugs. Skullcap has been used for more than 200 years as a mild relaxant and as a therapy for anxiety, nervous tension, and convulsions. Studies show American skullcap has significant antioxidant effects and may help protect against neurological disorders, such as Alzheimer's disease, Parkinson's disease, anxiety, and depression. It is also an antispasmodic herb that will relax muscles and help those suffering from nervous twitches, tics and headaches. Passion flower is used for anxiety and sleep problems, as well as for pain, heart rhythm problems, menopausal symptoms, and attention-deficit hyperactivity disorder. Hops is used for anxiety, inability to sleep (insomnia) and other sleep disorders, restlessness, tension, excitability, attention deficit-hyperactivity disorder (ADHD), nervousness, and irritability, stress and digestive upset. The herb is best known as a nervous system relaxant but also has pain-relieving, antimicrobial, antispasmodic, and diuretic properties. I wish you all good health!

I took 3 pills before going to bed and have been taking them for over a year. Now I am getting at least 4 hours of sound sleep a night. My oldest daughter's sleep problems are hereditary. She tosses and turns in bed for hours looking for a comfortable position. Unsuccessfully. And since sleep is extremely important for physical and mental health, after opening iHerb, I began to look for herbal preparations here to help cope with this age-old problem. Melatonin helps to fall asleep, but by the middle of the night its effect on the body stops and ... good morning. I wanted to find a remedy that would help prolong sleep. And after a long search, I found it! Of the many valerian-based complexes tried, this one worked much better than others! Apparently, here all these soothing herbs act synergistically and enhance the action of each other. Valerian root, as you know, has a good sedative effect and weakens the excitability of the nervous system, therefore it is used in the treatment of nervous disorders, insomnia, neurasthenia and other mental disorders of a chronic nature. By the way, in countries such as Germany and England, valerian has the status of sleeping pills. Skullcap also effectively eliminates anxiety, depression and headaches on nervous grounds, as well as improves sleep. It, like tannin and astragalus, has a sedative effect on the body, is used for chronic fatigue and neuroses, for the normalization of the central nervous system, and for insomnia too. What is good - it is not addictive and side effects. The Maya and Aztecs knew about the calming and relaxing effect of passionflower on the nervous system. Currently, passionflower preparations are used for neuro-vegetative dystonia, states of fear, anxiety and nervousness. It is used as a sedative for nervous disorders, anxiety, sleep disturbances and overexcitation. Hops, an important ingredient in any beer, have long been studied for sedation and have been used for centuries to treat sleep problems. Hops have also been used as a pillow filler. In England, for example, they have been popular since the days of Queen Victoria, who, like my daughter, also had a lot of trouble sleeping. Hop cones in folk medicine have long been known as a sedative and hypnotic. They normalize sleep, help in the fight against neuroses, cope with nervous excitability, have a beneficial effect on diseases of the nervous system - insomnia, neurasthenia, headaches, overexcitation. Could the complex have been created better? Maybe yes. I would also add chamomile and motherwort here ... but experts at Natural Factors considered it unnecessary. Well, they know better! Be that as it may - this complex "works"! It was not a panacea, but nevertheless, 2 capsules before bedtime, with mint or chamomile tea, really help calm down and prolong sleep. 🍃 Ladies and Gentlemen, I hope my reviews of the most popular supplements on iHerb will help you make your choice.

review_text: I have a long-standing problem with insomnia. And when the time zones changed with a difference of five hours, sleep ceased to exist at all. First, two capsules, then one. Valerian owes its sedative effect to a chemical compound that it accumulates in the roots. The main one is valeric acid. Therefore, the percentage of valeric acid is very important, because it shows the quantitative content of the active (active) substance in the preparation. And this is an assessment of the quality of plant materials. Our supplement has a good quantitative content of valerian and its acid.
